FINAL: Claude Shannon was born on April 30, 1916, and passed away on February 24, 2001. His three key contributions to information theory include: 1) The founding of information theory with his 1948 paper 'A Mathematical Theory of Communication', 2) The conceptualization of the bit as the fundamental unit of information, and 3) The development of the Shannon-Hartley theorem, which establishes the maximum rate at which information can be transmitted over a communications channel with a specified bandwidth in the presence of noise.
